item.title: Young Boy Strip Searched By TSA
item.description:
Young Boy Strip Searched By TSA
Very disgusting act. People can say "Oh it's for our safety". NO! This is complete B.S. I remember the day's before 9/11. The Only big explosions I had seen were in Summer Blockbusters. I remember that day like it was yesterday. I was 16, My Brother had left for Good `Ol Bootcamp in Great Lakes, Illinois Just north of Chicago just 5 days before the attacks (He's a Navy Vet). I remember the day he left. I remember the first thing I thought of when he was picked up. "Thank God, Were Not In A War". And then the morning of September 11th, I remember walking into the living room and overhearing the broadcast of Today. Katie Couric was talking about how a plane had flown into the WTC. My first thought was damn what an idiot, who the hell who be dumb enough to fly into the Trade Center. Then I remember watching That 2nd plane hit the building. It was the most shocking thing I had ever seen on TV. The first 3 weeks after the attack were unreal. I had never seen such patriotic people before. I swear it looked like every car was waving a flag on their car or atleast had an American sticker. The country really did seem United, we were an angry Country. Majority of people wanted to go after the Scum who did this at the start. I remember reading quotes from "Real Americans" like George Patton. I remember reading this quote before we first went into Afghanistan. "THE NAZI'S ARE THE ENEMY, WADE INTO THEM. SPILL THEIR BLOOD. SHOOT THEM IN THE BELLY. WHEN YOU PUT YOUR HAND INTO A BUNCH OF GOO THAT A MOMENT BEFORE WAS YOUR BEST FRIENDS FACE, YOU'LL KNOW WHAT TO DO" I must admit now that I'm ashamed of the way I felt, I wanted blood. I wanted the Death poored out on their families. But now I know a true Christian prays for his enemies. I dont know who to Pray for anymore. People have commented and said "The Terrorists Have Won" Why? because they've made some people afraid. They've won because this video was posted? and it put fear into people. I'm not afraid to go to an Airport, I'm not afraid to go to A Sporting Event. I'm sick and tired of hearing about when the next terror attack is going to happen. I'm sick of the mainstream media conditioning us like sheep. Trying to keep fear in us so they can do anything they want to us. Dont be leaving comments asking if I know the whole story? HELL YEAH I KNOW THE WHOLE STORY, IT WAS ME THAT GOT THIS VIDEO TO GO VIRAL. I"M THE ONE THAT CALLED THE NEWSTATIONS TO GET THIS OUT THERE.BECAUSE I LOVE MY COUNTRY AND I WAS OUTRAGED ENOUGH. FOR GODS SAKE LOOK WHAT YOUR WATCHING!! A LITTLE BOY BEING LEGALLY MOLESTED!! And NOTHINGS HAPPENING!! Their going to continue with this B.S. NO ONE HAS A RIGHT TO TOUCH YOUR BODY. A Cop isnt allowed To Touch you like that, even when your in a doctors office they arent quick to grab. I wouldnt be surprised if this country stages another attack just to get their laws passed to control you. Democrat or Republican their all BAD. They all want to achieve the same thing. If your now just starting to question the GOVT. you've been in the dark for a long time. If someone looks to make money of this or use this garbage for fame is Fucking twisted. I kept on thinking about Americans rights todays I cant even Imagine how that little kid feels right now. I'll be the first to say what kind of Dad do you have? WOW you threw your shirt at him. ASk yourself this, if that was your kid, would you just stand there? I can tell you this wouldnt have happened 10 years ago. Just think what the public will be 20.

item.title: Chievo - Inter 2-1 - Samuel Eto'o Headbutts Bostjan Cesar - November 21 2010 - [HD]
item.description:
Chievo - Inter 2-1 - Samuel Eto'o Headbutts Bostjan Cesar - November 21 2010 - [HD]
Inter Milan striker Samuel Eto'o may face disciplinary action after he was caught on camera headbutting Chievo Verona defender Bostjan Cesar on Sunday. The pair clashed in the 38th minute when Cesar threw a weak punch that hit Eto'o in the face. The Cameroon international jogged away before turning around and headbutting Cesar in the chest. Eto'o has been one of the few bright spots for defending European and Italian champion Inter, which has had to cope with injuries to key players and a loss of form. Eto'o has scored 17 goals in all competitions this season. The Italian league has used video evidence to ban Fiorentina striker Alberto Gilardino for two games after he scored a goal with his hand.
